Garreau model implementation

Garreau R, Bricca R, Gagnieu M-C, Roux S, Conrad A, Bet al. 2021. Population pharmacokinetics of daptomycin in patients with bone and joint infection: minimal effect of rifampicin co-administration and confirmation of a sex difference. J Antimicrob Chemother 76:1250–1257.

code_dapto<- "
[PARAM] @annotated
TVCL :  0.365  : Typical clearance
TVV1 : 3.59 : Typical central volume of distribution (L)
TVQ : 0.752 : Typical intercomp clearance 1 (L/h)
TVV2 : 4.71 : Typical peripheral volume of distribution 1 (L)
CLCR : 0.43 : effect of creatcl on cl
CLS : 0.232 : effect of sex on cl
VAG : 0.263 : effect of age on V
VWT: 0.603 : effect of WT on V
VS : 0.117 : effect of sex on V

ETA1 : 0 : ETA on TVCL
ETA2 : 0 : ETA on TVV1
ETA3 : 0 : ETA on TVQ
ETA4 : 0 : ETA on TVV2

$PARAM @annotated @covariates
CRCL : 109 : Typical creatinine CL (ml/min/1.73)
WT  : 79.2 : Typical wt (kg)
AGE : 60.4 : Typical age (year)
SEX : 1 : male

[CMT] @annotated
CENT : Central comaprtment (mg)
PERI : First peripheral compartment (mg)

[OMEGA] 0.036 0.015 1.27 0.0841

[MAIN]
double CL = TVCL * exp((CLCR*CRCL/109) + (CLS*SEX)) *exp(ETA1);
double V1 = TVV1 * exp((VAG*AGE/60.4) + (VWT * WT/79.2) + (VS * SEX)) * exp(ETA2);
double Q = TVQ * exp(ETA3);
double V2 = TVV2 * exp(ETA4);

[SIGMA] @annotated
PROP : 0.001 : proportionnal Residual unexplained variability 0.0496
ADD : 0.001 : additive Residual unexplained variability 2.55

[ODE]
dxdt_CENT =  -(CL+Q)*CENT/V1 + Q*PERI/V2;
dxdt_PERI = Q*CENT/V1 - Q*PERI/V2;

[TABLE]
capture DV = (CENT/V1)+ (ADD + PROP*(CENT/V1));
$CAPTURE DV CL
"

mod_dapto <- mcode("dapto_model", code_dapto)
## Building dapto_model ... done.

Patients simulation

set.seed(123456)
cov_data = tibble(ID = 1:200) %>% mutate(WT = rtruncnorm(n(),a=40, b=130, mean=79, sd=20),
                                        CRCL = rtruncnorm(n(),a=15, b=180, mean=101, sd=20),
                                        AGE = rtruncnorm(n(),a=18, b=90, mean=60, sd=16),
                                        SEX = rbinom(200,1, 0.6),
                                        TEMP= 37.2)

data_ev <- as_tibble(ev(ID = 1:100, amt = 8,ii=24, addl=4, tinf=0.5)) %>%
  mutate(dose_group = "8mg/kg") %>%
  bind_rows(as_tibble(ev(ID = 101:200, amt = 10,ii=24, addl=4, tinf=0.5))%>%
  mutate(dose_group = "10mg/kg")) %>% 
  arrange(ID) %>%
  left_join(cov_data) %>%
  mutate(amt = ceiling(WT*amt/10)*10, rate = amt/tinf)
## Joining with `by = join_by(ID)`
set.seed(1234)
sim <- mod_dapto %>% 
  data_set(data_ev) %>%
  # Req(DV) %>%
  mrgsim(end = 120, delta = 0.5) 

#Clean table
sim_dapto <- as_tibble(sim) %>% distinct(ID, time, .keep_all = TRUE) %>%
  left_join(data_ev %>% select(-time)) %>% 
  select(ID, time, DV, CL,amt,dose_group,  WT, CRCL,AGE, SEX, TEMP) %>%
  mutate(auc = amt/CL)

#Loading file
external_dataset <- dapto_auc_cohort %>% 
  mutate(Diff_C1C0 = conc_97 - conc_95.5) %>%
  rename(conc_C0 = conc_95.5,
         conc_C1 = conc_97)

## Filter 1_99 percentiles
centile_1_auc <- quantile(external_dataset$auc, 0.01)
centile_99_auc <- quantile(external_dataset$auc, 0.99)

centile_1_res <- quantile(external_dataset$conc_C0, 0.01)
centile_99_res <- quantile(external_dataset$conc_C0, 0.99)

centile_1_max <- quantile(external_dataset$conc_C1, 0.01)
centile_99_max <- quantile(external_dataset$conc_C1, 0.99)

external_dataset1 <- external_dataset %>%
  filter(auc >= centile_1_auc, auc <= centile_99_auc,
         conc_C0 >= centile_1_res, conc_C0 <= centile_99_res ,
         conc_C1 >= centile_1_max, conc_C1 <= centile_99_max)

Apply Xgboost model

model_xgb <- readRDS("auc_daptomycin_xgboost_1_99_res0_temp_filter.rds")

# new variable for prediction
auc_preds_xgb <- rep(NA, nrow(external_dataset))

# prediction
for (i in 1:nrow(external_dataset)) {
  predicteurs_patient_xgb <- external_dataset[
    i, c("WT", "CREATCL", "dose", "conc_C0", "conc_C1", "SEX","TEMP", "Diff_C1C0")]
  auc_pred_xgb <- predict(model_xgb, predicteurs_patient_xgb)
  auc_preds_xgb[i] <- auc_pred_xgb
}
## [16:11:49] WARNING: src/learner.cc:553: 
##   If you are loading a serialized model (like pickle in Python, RDS in R) generated by
##   older XGBoost, please export the model by calling `Booster.save_model` from that version
##   first, then load it back in current version. See:
## 
##     https://xgboost.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorials/saving_model.html
## 
##   for more details about differences between saving model and serializing.
external_dataset$auc_pred_xgb <- auc_preds_xgb
external_dataset$auc_pred_xgb <- as.numeric(external_dataset$auc_pred_xgb)
external_dataset <- external_dataset %>% 
  mutate(biais_brut = mean(auc_pred_xgb - external_dataset$auc),
         bias_rel = (auc_pred_xgb - external_dataset$auc) / external_dataset$auc,
         bias_rel_square = bias_rel^2,
         mse = mean((auc_pred_xgb - external_dataset$auc)^2),
         rmse = sqrt(mse),
         r2 = 1 - mse / var(external_dataset$auc))

summary_table <- external_dataset %>% 
  summarise(biais_brut = mean(biais_brut),
            biais_rel = mean(bias_rel),
            RMSE = mean(rmse),
            R2 = mean(r2),
            relative_rmse = sqrt(mean(bias_rel_square)),
            biais_out_20percent = mean(!dplyr::between(bias_rel, -0.2, 0.2)),
            nb_out_20percent = sum(!dplyr::between(bias_rel, -0.2, 0.2)),
            n = n())

rmarkdown::paged_table(as.data.frame(summary_table))

# Target AUC/CMI > 666, here proportion AUC >666 (dont forget to use CMI to categorise efficiency)
table_contingence_666 <- external_dataset %>% 
  mutate(event_auc = if_else(auc<=666,"inf_666","sup_666"), 
         event_xgb = if_else(auc_pred_xgb<=666,"inf_666","sup_666")) %>% 
  mutate_if(is.character, factor)
